'''GTK''' (the GIMP Toolkit) is [[Article description::a toolkit for creating graphical user interfaces.]] It is part of the GNU Project.

== Installation ==

Users can install the GTK libraries with the following command:

{{Emerge|x11-libs/gtk+}}

Some applications may optionally be built with support for a GTK interface when enabling the <code>gtk</code> <var>USE</var> flag.
Users may even choose to enable GTK support for all packages in {{Path|/etc/portage/make.conf}}.

